sketch.compiler.ast.core.typs

Class StructDef

  • java.lang.Object
    • sketch.compiler.ast.core.FENode
      • sketch.compiler.ast.core.typs.StructDef
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,Type>>

    public class StructDef
extends FENode
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,Type>>
    A hetereogeneous structure type. This type has a name for itself, and an ordered list of field names and types. You can retrieve the list of names, and the type a particular name maps to. The names must be unique within a given structure.

    There is an important assumption in testing for equality and type promotions: two structure types are considered equal if they have the same name, regardless of any other characteristics. This allows structures and associated structure-reference types to sanely compare equal.

    This is the "definition" of a structure which contains not only the struct name, but also the information of its fields. On the contrary, TypeStructRef just refers to a struct by its name.
